  "text": "As in developing countries today, there was significant underutilization of labor in Many of these workers lacked a job that offered steady income. The common practice of sharing work and income among family members in rural areas meant that remaining family members would work more if some members left for the cities. A withdrawal of part of the work force could, therefore, leave production unchanged. Thus, according to the production test of employment [CITATION_1] , there was widespread disguised rural unemployment throughout the inter-war years.",
